<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1952-03-26T05:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-03-26T05:30:00-05:00" n="824" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d824">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">601.8990D/3–2652: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Afghanistan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MGR1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Merrell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d824fn1">This telegram was repeated for information to
                                    London and Karachi.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Kabul</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1952-03-26T15:00:00+04:30">March 26, 1952—3
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>406. <gloss target="#t_PriMin1">PriMin</gloss><note n="2" xml:id="d824fn2"><persName>Shah Mahmud Ghazi</persName>.</note>
                                informed me this morning that an Afghan <gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss> wld not be sent to Karachi until the <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> Govt had accepted the fourth point
                                of the November 7 proposal.<note n="3" xml:id="d824fn3">Reference is
                                    to the U.S. initiative of Nov. 6, 1950. See <ref target="#d823fn4">footnote 4, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi></ref>.</note> He seemed pleased however that
                                    <persName corresp="#p_SCASB1">Shah</persName><note n="4" xml:id="d824fn4">Col. <persName corresp="#p_SCASB1">A. S. B.
                                        Shah</persName>.</note> is coming to Kabul as <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss><gloss target="#t_Amb1">Amb</gloss>
                                and appeared to hope that some good might come of the appt.</p>
                            <p>When I told him that while in Wash I had been much disappointed to
                                learn of a recrudescence of Afghan propaganda against <gloss target="#t_Pak1">Pak</gloss> he admitted this had occurred but
                                said that “slowly slowly it wld die out”.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_MGR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Merrell</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>